     Diversity at the FDIC
   About FDIC: Jobs@FDIC
     __________________________________________________________________

   The FDIC requires the expertise and hard work of a diverse staff to
   meet its mandate to supervise the management of banks and savings &
   loans, ensure compliance with fair credit and community reinvestment
   statutes, and help foster economic stability in the USA.

   The FDIC has its headquarters in Washington, D.C. It also staffs eight
   regional offices -- in Atlanta, Boston, Chicago, Dallas, Kansas City,
   Memphis, New York, and San Francisco -- and more than 90 field offices
   throughout the country.
     * All Job Opportunities
       All FDIC jobs currently being advertised.

     Executive Positions
     Senior leaders responsible for defining and directing the FDIC
     mission.
     Internships
     Summer jobs and career-launching opportunities for highly motivated
     students.
     Examiners
     If your background includes study of accounting, business management
     or a related field, learn more about Careers in Supervision.
     Compliance Examiners
     If your background includes accounting, community development, civil
     rights or consumer protection expertise learn more about Careers as
     Bank Compliance Examiners.

     * How to Apply
       Instructions on applying for a job and an easy-to-complete
       application form.

